<TITLE> Shoe factory gutted at Lalbagh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 16 (bdnews24.com)A shoe factory on the ground floor of a five-storey residential building caught fire on Thursday at Islambagh of Lalbagh in the old part of the capital. The incident took place at around 1:30pm, Dilip Kumar Ghosh, the deputy assistant director at Dhaka Southern Zone of Fire Service and Civil Defence, told bdnews24.com. He said firemen with 10 vehicles, including two from Lalbagh and Palashi stations each, doused the fire at around 3pm. The fire might have been originated from electric short-circuit, sub-inspector Mashiur Rahman, in charge of Lalbagh Zone Police Post, told bdnews24.com. Some four workers were at the factory when the fire broke out, he said. Shahjahan Rahman Shaju, owner of the factory and the building, said he had started the factory four years ago. 'Ismail', a neighbour who witnessed the incident, said locals rushed to the site after residents of the building had shouted for help. They initially tried to douse the fire and informed the fire services. Three people of the upper floor of the building fainted as smoke choked them, Rahman said. None suffered any burn injury, he also said. bd
